@startuml
title Viaverse Release Gate / Go-Live Decision — Sequence Diagram

participant "Product Lead" as PM
participant "GitHub / CI" as Repo
participant "QA" as QA
participant "Security/Privacy" as Sec
participant "Platform/Ops" as Ops
participant "Observability" as Obs
participant "Admin/Support" as Admin
participant "Release Owner" as Release

PM -> Repo : tag release candidate
Repo -> QA : build + test artifacts
Repo -> Sec : SAST/dependency/IaC scan
Repo -> Ops : deploy to staging
Ops -> Obs : smoke + metrics
QA -> Release : QA signoff
Sec -> Release : security/privacy signoff
Obs -> Release : SLO/error budget signoff
Admin -> Release : support/admin readiness
Release ..> Repo : promote or block

note bottom
Go-live requires product acceptance, QA evidence,
security/privacy review, operational readiness,
observability and rollback plan.
end note
@enduml
